            . I am a journeyman pawnbroker in Jermyn-street, St. James's; I took in this watch (produced in court, and deposed to) of the prisoner at the bar, on the 2d of August; he said his name was Trevor, I lent him a guinea on it; he came again the Thursday night was fortnight, he said he wanted 5 s. 3 d. more on it, or to sell it outright; I had seen the advertisement on the 3d of August, and carried the watch, so I stopped him, and he was committed.</p>
